  <Annotation SID="8040">
    <P Name="Name">
EITHER ABS is switched on and  S_K is put through
 when S_K is becomming bigger the s_{ku} 
OR output is 0 when S_K is smaller than {sku}_{off}
</P>
    <P Name="Position">[369, 26, 595, 95]</P>
    <P Name="InternalMargins">[0, 0, 0, 0]</P>
    <P Name="DropShadow">on</P>
    <P Name="Interpreter">tex</P>
    <P Name="ZOrder">-1</P>
  </Annotation>
  <Annotation SID="8041">
    <P Name="Name">
Valve Control:
Valves are open for a predefined time window. 
The driving time depends on a trigger criterion (LUT).
The treshold change for the valve driving time is 
continously modified by a repeating sequence.
</P>
    <P Name="Position">[757, 27, 993, 120]</P>
    <P Name="InternalMargins">[0, 0, 0, 0]</P>
    <P Name="DropShadow">on</P>
    <P Name="ZOrder">-2</P>
  </Annotation>
  <Annotation SID="8042">
    <P Name="Name">
Control strategy: Trigger criterion S_K
S_K combines wheel decceleration control with slip control 
using weighting factors  K_z and K_\lambda
S_K=K_z*z_R + K_\lambda * \lambda_{rel}
(see p.127 in M. Burckhardt 
Fahrwerktechnik:Radschlupfregelsysteme)
</P>
    <P Name="Position">[54, 27, 311, 134]</P>
    <P Name="InternalMargins">[0, 0, 0, 0]</P>
    <P Name="DropShadow">on</P>
    <P Name="Interpreter">tex</P>
    <P Name="ZOrder">-3</P>
  </Annotation>
</System>

